name: Human metapneumovirus HMPV outbreak
summary: China has witnessed a surge in cases of human metapneumovirus (HMPV), a respiratory virus. The virus, which typically causes mild respiratory illnesses, has become a concern due to its high prevalence and potential to cause severe infections in vulnerable populations such as young children, the elderly, and immunocompromised individuals. Neighboring countries have taken note of the outbreak and are monitoring the situation. China has characterized the outbreak as a "winter occurrence" and downplayed the severity, while other countries like India have advised citizens not to panic. Health authorities are urging people to take precautions such as practicing good hygiene and seeking medical attention if symptoms persist. The virus can be spread through respiratory droplets released into the air when an infected person coughs or sneezes. Symptoms of HMPV infection can include fever, cough, runny nose, and sore throat. While the virus is usually mild, it can lead to complications such as pneumonia, bronchiolitis, and severe respiratory distress in certain individuals.

name: Three Kings Day
summary: Three Kings Day, celebrated on January 6th, is a significant holiday in many cultures, including the DMV area. Known as Día de los Reyes in Spanish, this day commemorates the biblical story of the Three Wise Men visiting the infant Jesus. Celebrations range from parades and toy distributions to special religious observances. In the DMV, festivities include the Three Kings Day Parade in New York City and the toy distribution in Hartford, Connecticut. Some states are considering recognizing Three Kings Day as a state holiday, recognizing its religious and cultural significance. The holiday serves as a reminder of faith, traditions, and the importance of giving, with parades, religious services, and community gatherings bringing people together to celebrate the Epiphany.

name: Trump inauguration
summary: On January 20th, 2025, Donald Trump's second inauguration as president of the United States will take place on Martin Luther King Jr. Day. The inauguration will come after Trump's victory in the 2024 election, which saw him raise over $200 million in campaign funds since Election Day. Despite legal challenges, Trump's inauguration will proceed as planned, following a judge's denial of his request to stop his impending sentencing. Meanwhile, Apple CEO Tim Cook has donated $1 million to the Trump inauguration fund. Joe Biden's comments about avoiding Trump at the inauguration have been misquoted. Trump plans to hold a rally in Washington, D.C., on January 19th, the day before his inauguration. It is a rare occurrence for Inauguration Day to fall on a federal holiday. U.S. flags will be flown at half-staff in honor of former President Jimmy Carter, whose recent health issues prompted Trump's condolences and a statement of appreciation.
